RULE X — CLAIM ISOLATION
  ▎ You are rating one thing: the extracted claim, exactly as stated. Nothing else.                            
  ▎ Any other assertions you encounter during research — related claims in the same article, contextual        
  background about the subject, other statements attributed to the same person or source — are irrelevant. Do  
  not import them into the verdict.                                                                            
  ▎ If the claim is "Quran manuscript is 1,400 years old", the fact that search results also discuss authorship
   attribution is background noise. Rate the age claim. Stop there.                                            
  ▎ Corollary: HALF TRUE requires two separable assertions both present in the extracted claim as stated. 
  Sub-claims found only in research context do not count.         
  
  
  

